This paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the concept of pairwise compatibility graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves the study of graphs with a small number of vertices, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of the structure of trees, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
